===Etymology 3===
{{ja-kanjitab|あららぎ|yomi=k}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=|-}}, first attested in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' (720 {{CE}}).<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Any further derivation is unclear. Speculative possibilities include:
* The initial ''ara-'' may be cognate with {{m|ja|荒い|tr=arai||rough; wild}}. The final ''-ragi'' is unknown, however.
* Alternatively, the initial ''arara-'' may be cognate with {{m|ja|荒らか|tr=araraka||rough; wild}}. The final ''-gi'' may be cognate with {{m|ja|木|tr=ki||tree}}, perhaps in reference to the way the plant's stalk rises straight and tall.

